physical_examinations.relevant_findings: The posterior neck and occipital region on the left side were tender but had full range of motion; remainder of the examination was normal.

The remainder of the examination was normal. An electrocardiogram showed sinus rhythm with a ventricular rate of 101 bpm and presented first-degree atrioventricular block and right bundle-branch block.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: First-degree atrioventricular block and right bundle-branch block were present and had not been present 3 years earlier.
